Preheat your oven to 150°C. Chop the @cherry plum tomatoes{200%g} in half. Trim the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1} and half lengthways, then thinly slice widthways. Grate the @carrot{1}(grated) on a coarse #grater{} (no need to peel). Halve, then remove the core from the @bell pepper{1} and chop into small pieces. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Remove the @super soft tortillas with whole wheat{2} from their packaging, wrap them in #foil{}, and place on a #baking tray{} on the middle shelf of your oven to warm up for ~{10%minutes}.

Heat a glug of @oil{glug} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Once hot, add the @lamb mince{400%g} and brown for ~{5-7%minutes}, breaking up with a #wooden spoon{} as it cooks. Drain off any excess fat. Add the carrot, red pepper and @dried thyme{1%tsp}. Lower the heat to medium and cook for another ~{5%minutes} then add the @tomato puree{2%tbsp}, tomatoes and two-thirds of the @caramelised red onion relish{1/3%jar}. Bubble away until thick, ~{5%minutes}. Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @ground black pepper{to taste}.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{} mix the @Greek style natural yoghurt{150%g}, the remaining caramelised red onion relish and a pinch of salt and pepper. This is your sauce, set aside.

Once the tortilla wraps are warm, lay out one per person on a #plate{}. Add a handful of lettuce to the centre of the wrap, top with a spoonful of the lamb mixture, followed by a drizzle of sauce and a sprinkling of parsley.

Roll up or fold over the wraps, however you prefer to eat them and leave the leftovers on the side to make seconds! Enjoy!

> These Henley Regata Lamb Wraps are an all time family favourite. We have made them quick and easy for you to knock-up in just six steps!